#Ingredients

10 oz ground pork
2 cloves of garlic
2 Tbsps Tomato Paste	
1 bunch of kale
2 Tbsps Macarpone Cheese
6 0z Cavatappi Pasta 
2 Tbsps Dired Currants
1/4 cup Grated Romana Cheese
1tsp Quatre Espices

Spice Blends 
# Quare Espices
2 parts ground white pepper
1 part gorund ginger
1 part ground nutmeg
1 part ground cloves

1 Prepare the ingredients 
(*) Fill a medium pot 3/4 of the way up with salted water; cover and heat to boiling on high 
(*) Place currants in a bowl Cover 1/4/ cuipof hot water Set asaide to rehydrate (at least ten minutes)
(*) Wash and dry the kale; separete  the leaves from teh stems. Dicard teh stems, then thinly slice the leaves 
(*) Peel and roughly chop 2 cloves of garlic 

2 Cook the Pasta 
(*) Add the pasta to the pot of boiling water. Cook,strring occasionally, 7 to 9 minutes, or until al dente 
(*) Reserving 1/2 cup of the pasta water, drain thoroughly 

3 Cook the Pork and Make the Ragu
(*) Meanwhile in a large pan, heat 2 teaspoons of olive oil on medium-high heat
(*) Add the pork, chopoped garlic, and spice blend; season with salt and pepper.  
(*) Cook stiring frequently and breaking meat apart 3-4 minutes.
(*) Add tomato past season with salt and pepper.  cook constantly stirring for 1-2 minutes
(*) Add 3/4 cup of water season with salt and pepper 
(*) Add sliced kale and currants (including liquid). Cover pan with foil for 3-4 minutes
(*) Remove foil stir to combine 

4 Finish 
(*) Add cooked pasta and water
(*) Cook stirring for 1-2 minutes or until the pasta water is gone
(*) Stir in Mascarpone cheese until combined 
(*) garnish with romano
